  <div class="container">
    <header>
      <h1>The Power of Mindful Productivity</h1>
      <address>By <strong>Jane Smith</strong> | Published on <time datetime="2025-06-06">June 6, 2025</time></address>
    </header>

    <article>
      <p>In today's fast-paced world, productivity has become a buzzword—but what if we told you that slowing down could actually help you do more?</p>

      <h2>What is Mindful Productivity?</h2>
      <p>Mindful productivity is the practice of approaching work with intention, focus, and awareness. Instead of multitasking and burning out, you take deliberate steps to prioritize and perform better.</p>

      <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/750x300" alt="A person meditating at a desk with a laptop">

      <h2>Key Benefits</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Improved focus and attention span</li>
        <li>Reduced stress and anxiety levels</li>
        <li>Greater job satisfaction and creativity</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Simple Tips to Start</h2>
      <p>Here are a few ways you can start applying mindful productivity today:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Start your day with 5 minutes of deep breathing</li>
        <li>Work in focused 25-minute sessions (Pomodoro Technique)</li>
        <li>Take regular, tech-free breaks</li>
      </ul>

      <p>Remember, productivity isn’t about doing more—it’s about doing what matters, better.</p>
    </article>

